### Configure LangGraph Tool Validation and JSONPatch Retries in Python

Source: https://github.com/langchain-ai/langgraph/blob/main/docs/docs/tutorials/extraction/retries.ipynb

This Python code defines an exception formatter (`format_exception`) for tool call errors, providing detailed feedback including the error and expected schema. It then configures a `ValidationNode` with a list of tools including `PatchFunctionParameters` to allow JSONPatch for corrections, and initializes a `RetryStrategy` to manage multiple attempts and fallbacks. Finally, it integrates these components using `_bind_validator_with_retries` to create a robust tool execution pipeline with built-in error handling and self-correction capabilities.

```python
    def format_exception(error: BaseException, call: ToolCall, schema: Type[BaseModel]):
        return (
            f"Error:\n\n```\n{repr(error)}\n```\n"
            "Expected Parameter Schema:\n\n" + f"```json\n{schema.schema_json()}\n```\n"
            f"Please respond with a JSONPatch to correct the error for tool_call_id=[{call['id']}]."
        )

    validator = ValidationNode(
        tools + [PatchFunctionParameters],
        format_error=format_exception,
    )
    retry_strategy = RetryStrategy(
        max_attempts=max_attempts,
        fallback=fallback_llm,
        aggregate_messages=aggregate_messages,
    )
    return _bind_validator_with_retries(
        bound_llm,
        validator=validator,
        retry_strategy=retry_strategy,
        tool_choice=tool_choice,
    ).with_config(metadata={"retry_strategy": "jsonpatch"})
```

