### Customize Langchain Agent Tool Error Handling

Source: https://github.com/langchain-ai/langgraph/blob/main/docs/docs/how-tos/tool-calling.md

Shows how to explicitly configure a `ToolNode` to customize or disable the default error handling behavior in Langchain agents. This provides granular control over how tool errors are managed, allowing for custom messages or specific error responses.

```python
custom_tool_node = ToolNode(
    [multiply],
    handle_tool_errors="Cannot use 42 as a first operand!"
)

agent_custom = create_react_agent(
    model="anthropic:claude-3-7-sonnet-latest",
    tools=custom_tool_node
)

agent_custom.invoke({"messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "what's 42 x 7?"}]})
```

